Built and registered the rollback plan for `ART-122`. The new generator at [scripts/generate_art122_rollback.py](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/scripts/generate_art122_rollback.py) now produces the canonical markdown at [migration-artifacts/07-cutover/rollback-plan.md](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/migration-artifacts/07-cutover/rollback-plan.md), the task-scoped companions in [migration-artifacts/art-122_rollback](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/migration-artifacts/art-122_rollback), the report at [generated/art122_rollback_report.json](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/generated/art122_rollback_report.json), and the proof/heartbeat/log outputs including [proof_records/ART-122_ROLLBACK.proof.json](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/proof_records/ART-122_ROLLBACK.proof.json).

The rollback plan captures four branches: verify-only preflight, safe artifact-only failback from the repeat-safe checkpoint, task-scoped cleanup for `ART-122` outputs, and approval-gated restore from `history/pre_execution_framework_manifest.json`. It also explicitly records the current blockers for reattempting after rollback: `REQ-041_TWO_REPO_INTEGRATION`, `REQ-045_RUN_REPLAY`, and `VER-300_UNIT_VALIDATION`.

Verification passed. I ran `python3 -m py_compile scripts/generate_art122_rollback.py` and `python3 scripts/generate_art122_rollback.py`; the generated report shows all three artifact rows registered with content hashes and validation links, and `generated/status_from_proofs.json` now includes `ART-122_ROLLBACK` as completed. The worktree was already dirty before this task, so I kept my changes scoped to the rollback artifact path and its supporting generator/proof outputs.
